The first fatality was recorded on Friday when a pedestrian was killed outside De Doorns. CAPE TOWN At least six people have died on Western Cape Roads since Friday and with the Easter period not over yet, provincial traffic officials have urged motorists to be alert.The first fatality was recorded on Friday when a pedestrian was killed outside De Doorns.A motorcyclist and his passenger were also killed over the weekend in a head-on collision in Matroosfontein.It is understood they were not wearing their helmets at the time of the accident.Traffic Chief Kenny Africa said, Early this morning we had an accident on Robert Sobukwe Road where two cars collided and one person died. 